Magnesium.why: Lack of magnesium can cause blood vessels to constrict, leading to headache. Magnesium also plays a role in regulating neurotransmitters and muscle function, which can contribute to headache development.
Magnesium.tip: Take a warm bath with Epsom salt to help relax muscles and increase magnesium absorption.

Vitamin B2 (Riboflavin).why: Lack of vitamin B2 can lead to impaired energy production in cells, causing headache. Vitamin B2 also helps regulate homocysteine levels, which can contribute to headache development.
Vitamin B2 (Riboflavin).tip: Reduce stress through meditation or deep breathing exercises, as stress can exacerbate vitamin B2 imbalance.

Iron.why: Lack of iron can cause a decrease in oxygen delivery to tissues, leading to headache. Iron also plays a role in regulating dopamine and serotonin levels, which can contribute to headache development.
Iron.tip: Exercise regularly to improve blood flow and increase iron utilization.
